HEADWORD: Hoppo
<hw>Hop"po</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A
collector of customs, as at Canton; an overseer of commerce.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A tribunal or commission having charge of the revenue
derived from trade and navigation.</def> <mark>[China]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hoppo men</b></col>, <cd>Chinese customhouse
officers.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

